WEBVTT

00:07.507 --> 00:08.758
- What brings you two
to Akumal?

00:08.800 --> 00:10.135
- It's our
ten year anniversary.

00:10.176 --> 00:11.845
Holy shit.
[screams]

00:11.886 --> 00:13.346
- This phone belonged
to Sam Lawford

00:13.388 --> 00:14.931
who went missing 15 years ago.

00:14.973 --> 00:16.349
- [gasps]
Holy shit.

00:16.391 --> 00:18.059
- Violet Thompson
was also reported missing.

00:18.101 --> 00:21.354
- Baltasar Frías,
who was our prime suspect.

00:21.396 --> 00:24.190
But the storm
washed everything away

00:24.232 --> 00:26.026
before I got any evidence.

00:26.067 --> 00:28.445
- Em, you should see this.

00:28.486 --> 00:29.654
- Which means that
that's the pent--

00:29.696 --> 00:31.573
[gasps]
That's Sam and Violet!

00:31.614 --> 00:33.533
* *

00:33.575 --> 00:35.035
- [gasps, screams]
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

00:35.076 --> 00:36.703
- I met a guy.

00:36.745 --> 00:37.871
We have a date tonight.

00:37.912 --> 00:39.080
- [chuckles]

00:40.415 --> 00:41.666
- I found your board.

00:41.708 --> 00:43.043
- What skateboard?

00:43.084 --> 00:44.336
- Hey!
- [grunts]

00:44.377 --> 00:45.587
- [gasps]
Sam?

00:45.628 --> 00:48.548
* *

00:54.637 --> 00:56.348
- Man, Creepy Santa
keeps getting creepier.

00:56.389 --> 00:57.766
[elevator dings]
Oh, shit.

01:01.144 --> 01:02.228
- [whispering]
That's Baltasar Frías.

01:02.270 --> 01:03.897
He's got the phone.

01:03.938 --> 01:05.523
* *

01:05.565 --> 01:07.400
- [yelps]

01:07.442 --> 01:09.277
[phone buzzing]
- No!

01:11.696 --> 01:13.365
- [yelps]

01:14.407 --> 01:17.452
[indistinct shouting]

01:18.995 --> 01:21.623
[phone buzzing]
- No!

01:23.625 --> 01:25.126
[clattering]

01:26.878 --> 01:28.380
[grunting]

01:28.421 --> 01:31.508
[tense music]

01:31.549 --> 01:35.095
[grunting]

01:35.136 --> 01:41.059
* *

01:41.101 --> 01:42.560
- What are you doing?

01:42.602 --> 01:44.562
- I figured we could, like,

01:44.604 --> 01:46.606
lock him in a closet
or something.

01:46.648 --> 01:48.274
- No, no, no, no, no.
We can't just leave him here.

01:48.316 --> 01:49.401
- Why not?
He's clearly not dead.

01:49.442 --> 01:50.610
- What were you even thinking?

01:50.652 --> 01:51.903
- I couldn't let
him take the phone.

01:51.945 --> 01:52.987
- So you tried to kill him?

01:53.029 --> 01:54.155
- He's fine.
- [moans]

01:54.197 --> 01:55.740
- Oh!

01:55.782 --> 01:57.534
- [whispers] The phone rang.
Did you see that?

01:57.575 --> 01:59.953
- What--what--what are you
even talking about...

01:59.994 --> 02:01.079
- The phone rang.
- Right now?

02:01.121 --> 02:03.039
- [screaming]
- Ah, fuck! Fuck.

02:03.081 --> 02:05.500
- It's okay. It's okay.
It's okay. It's okay.

02:06.501 --> 02:09.337
[grunts]
[panting]

02:10.839 --> 02:14.926
- What an unusual turn
of events.

02:16.052 --> 02:17.721
- What are you doing here?

02:17.762 --> 02:20.098
- Well, I heard
you found the phone.

02:20.140 --> 02:21.975
- Who told you that?

02:22.017 --> 02:23.643
- An old friend.

02:23.685 --> 02:24.853
- Oh, Luna.

02:24.894 --> 02:26.312
- Yeah, where is--
where is the phone now?

02:26.354 --> 02:27.856
- It's in a million pieces

02:27.897 --> 02:29.816
at the bottom of the fucking
elevator shaft because of you.

02:29.858 --> 02:32.110
- No, the impulse to destroy it
came from you.

02:32.152 --> 02:33.319
- Hey, maybe you
should sit down, man.

02:33.361 --> 02:36.364
- I'm okay.
- Sit the fuck down!

02:36.406 --> 02:37.699
- But, Em, chill out.
- What?

02:37.741 --> 02:39.034
We don't know what
he's going to do.

02:39.075 --> 02:40.285
He's acting like
a loose cannon.

02:40.326 --> 02:41.494
- Yeah, well,
you have the weapon,

02:41.536 --> 02:44.539
and I have not provoked you
in any way.

02:46.875 --> 02:49.627
- What did you do
to Sam and Violet?

02:50.754 --> 02:54.758
- You--you think
I did something to them?

02:55.967 --> 02:58.053
- Yeah.
- Why?

02:58.094 --> 02:59.971
- 'Cause you had
Sam's skateboard,

03:00.013 --> 03:03.433
and because I know about
you and your family.

03:05.268 --> 03:08.438
- And that's all
of your evidence?

03:10.565 --> 03:13.318
[chuckles] Let me--
let me tell you something.

03:13.360 --> 03:17.072
I come from a family
of tailors, hmm?

03:17.113 --> 03:18.698
Not murderers.

03:18.740 --> 03:21.910
So if this is where
your investigation has led you,

03:21.951 --> 03:26.748
I'm not sure you're capable of
believing the true story, hmm?

03:28.124 --> 03:31.670
[panting]
What are your names?

03:33.797 --> 03:37.133
Okay, don't tell me.
Are you guys married?

03:37.175 --> 03:39.552
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, oh, okay.

03:39.594 --> 03:40.970
I think it's time to go.

03:41.012 --> 03:42.889
You--you seem good.

03:42.931 --> 03:45.684
This all seems to be
a big misunderstanding, so--

03:45.725 --> 03:49.854
- Well, maybe, maybe we can
understand it together, no?

03:52.148 --> 03:54.901
- What's the true story?

03:54.943 --> 03:56.569
- [sighs]

03:56.611 --> 03:58.571
What happened
to Sam and Violet

03:58.613 --> 04:01.491
is just one thread
in a tapestry

04:01.533 --> 04:05.370
of interconnected stories.

04:05.412 --> 04:07.580
[sighs]

04:07.622 --> 04:10.333
Everything comes back
to the Oceana Vista

04:10.375 --> 04:13.128
and the tragic demise

04:13.169 --> 04:16.464
of its misunderstood owner,

04:16.506 --> 04:19.592
Alexander Vasilakis.

04:19.634 --> 04:22.804
No one knew exactly
where Alex came from.

04:22.846 --> 04:25.390
One rumor was that
he just wandered

04:25.432 --> 04:27.142
out of the jungle one day

04:27.183 --> 04:30.145
with only a dream
of opening a resort.

04:30.186 --> 04:32.731
A more accepted rumor
was that he was born

04:32.772 --> 04:34.315
in a family
of hedge fund managers,

04:34.357 --> 04:37.152
and then he stole a yacht
and moved to Quintana Roo

04:37.193 --> 04:40.405
to start his own path.

04:40.447 --> 04:43.491
Alex possessed
a profound human insight

04:43.533 --> 04:46.536
and belief
in the potential of others.

04:46.578 --> 04:48.663
But let me be clear.

04:48.705 --> 04:53.376
This man was not
a brilliant man.

04:53.418 --> 04:55.670
- You into
metaphysical shit, man?

04:58.506 --> 05:01.760
- I am not sure what you mean.

05:03.219 --> 05:04.804
- Good answer.

05:04.846 --> 05:06.348
Sit.

05:06.389 --> 05:07.640
- Yes.

05:11.353 --> 05:15.565
- And you are Baltasar Peniche?

05:15.607 --> 05:18.985
- Yes, sir. Yes.
- It sounds made-up.

05:19.027 --> 05:22.364
So you are applying for--

05:22.405 --> 05:23.615
- Any job.

05:23.656 --> 05:25.742
I heard you were
hiring all positions.

05:25.784 --> 05:28.161
- Bold move--
or the move of a fickle man

05:28.203 --> 05:30.997
who doesn't know what he wants,
so what exactly do you want?

05:31.039 --> 05:33.500
- Like, in life, or--

05:33.541 --> 05:36.503
- Because I get this feeling

05:36.544 --> 05:38.254
like you're running
from something,

05:38.296 --> 05:40.006
rather than running towards it.

05:43.635 --> 05:45.470
Let's go to the beach.

05:45.512 --> 05:48.431
So why here, Peniche?
Why this resort?

05:48.473 --> 05:50.975
- Because you're hiring?

05:51.017 --> 05:52.602
- That's true.
Thanks for the honesty.

05:52.644 --> 05:54.145
Yeah, we're hiring.

05:54.187 --> 05:58.400
But it's more of a factory
where we mass produce

05:58.441 --> 06:02.028
the single most precious thing
that humans are capable of.

06:02.070 --> 06:06.157
- Hm. Children.
- No, no, no, memories.

06:06.199 --> 06:08.243
- Oh. Yeah.
- Memories.

06:08.284 --> 06:10.995
- Memories can be bad, too, no?

06:13.456 --> 06:15.750
- Thumb wrestle.
Let's do it.

06:16.584 --> 06:18.795
One, two, three, four.
I declare a thumb war.

06:18.837 --> 06:20.547
You're not even trying.
What are you doing?

06:20.588 --> 06:21.715
- okay, okay, I know, I know.

06:21.756 --> 06:25.051
- Okay.
If you win, you get the job.

06:25.093 --> 06:28.054
One, two, three, four.
I declare a thumb war.

06:28.096 --> 06:29.556
All right, rapid fire.

06:29.597 --> 06:31.391
What is your first memory
of joy, motherfucker?

06:31.433 --> 06:33.226
- Um, I don't know, sir.
- Try.

06:33.268 --> 06:34.936
- I've had a complicated life.
- Okay, cool, me too.

06:34.978 --> 06:36.896
Everyone does.
But it all starts from joy.

06:36.938 --> 06:38.648
The first memory is joy, and
everything springs from that.

06:38.690 --> 06:40.692
So what the fuck is it?
- Uh, reading.

06:40.734 --> 06:42.235
I like reading, sir.
- Terrible reader over here.

06:42.277 --> 06:43.570
What are we reading?

06:43.611 --> 06:44.988
- Detective novels.
- Why detective novels?

06:45.030 --> 06:46.656
- Because my father gave me
those when I was a kid.

06:46.698 --> 06:49.159
- Okay, you and your father
were close?

06:49.200 --> 06:50.577
Come on!
Don't stop!

06:50.618 --> 06:52.203
- The reason I like
detective novels, sir,

06:52.245 --> 06:53.455
is because I understand them.

06:53.496 --> 06:54.914
They raise questions
that always have answers.

06:54.956 --> 06:57.500
They try to answer both
the mystery of a crime

06:57.542 --> 06:58.835
and the mystery of life.
- Ah, come on!

06:58.877 --> 07:00.920
- And I like the characters!
- Which characters?

07:00.962 --> 07:02.630
- The detectives, sir!
- Why the detectives?

07:02.672 --> 07:04.215
- Because they're obsessed
and alone

07:04.257 --> 07:06.009
and they're home is on the edge
of the void of hopelessness.

07:06.051 --> 07:07.302
- That's why
you like detectives?

07:07.344 --> 07:08.303
That is so fucking weird,
Peniche.

07:08.345 --> 07:09.596
- They want to do
the right thing,

07:09.637 --> 07:10.597
even if that kills them.

07:10.638 --> 07:11.723
It's for a greater good.

07:11.765 --> 07:12.891
- You think
it's gonna kill you?

07:12.932 --> 07:14.142
- I don't know!
I don't know, sir!

07:14.184 --> 07:15.477
Ah!
Ah!

07:15.518 --> 07:16.770
I don't know!
I don't know!

07:16.811 --> 07:18.188
- Do you feel alone?
- Yes!

07:18.229 --> 07:20.106
- Is there a world
in which joy and loneliness

07:20.148 --> 07:22.067
can exist in harmony?
- Yeah, sometimes!

07:22.108 --> 07:23.526
- But do you want
to be alone, Peniche?

07:23.568 --> 07:25.403
Do you want to be alone?
- No, I don't want to be alone!

07:25.445 --> 07:26.654
I don't want to be alone!

07:26.696 --> 07:28.031
- Then what do you want
to be, Peniche?

07:28.073 --> 07:30.116
- I want to be
a detective, sir!

07:30.158 --> 07:31.618
[both panting]

07:31.659 --> 07:34.329
- Then be one,
you son of a bitch.

07:34.371 --> 07:36.247
[chuckles]

07:36.289 --> 07:38.333
- We became fast friends.

07:39.209 --> 07:41.461
Alex personally hired
every employee

07:41.503 --> 07:42.962
of theirs in the vista,

07:43.004 --> 07:46.675
each one a lost soul
running from their past.

07:46.716 --> 07:48.718
We had Edwin,
a glass cutter from Honduras

07:48.760 --> 07:50.387
heading concierge.

07:50.428 --> 07:52.514
[radio clicks]
[speaking Spanish]

07:53.848 --> 07:56.601
Patricia,
a runaway nun from Tampico

07:56.643 --> 07:58.186
on my security team.

07:58.228 --> 08:00.605
Abigail, an actual fugitive
from Puerto Rico,

08:00.647 --> 08:02.357
chief landscaper.

08:02.399 --> 08:03.775
She was arrested for stealing

08:03.817 --> 08:05.902
and then crashing
the governor's helicopter.

08:05.944 --> 08:07.737
But most dear to me was Luna,

08:07.779 --> 08:09.656
who lost her family
in a car accident.

08:09.698 --> 08:11.032
She became my sister.

08:11.074 --> 08:13.243
So then began
what vacationers referred to

08:13.284 --> 08:15.203
as the sandcastle days.

08:15.245 --> 08:18.331
And whatever sprung from
the odd garden of Alex's mind

08:18.373 --> 08:21.167
found its way into the fabric
of the Oceana Vista.

08:21.209 --> 08:22.460
- [laughs]
Ah!

08:22.502 --> 08:26.006
[phone ringing]

08:26.047 --> 08:27.799
- He used to call me at dawn

08:27.841 --> 08:30.844
and leave me messages
about dreams he had.

08:30.885 --> 08:32.929
- We were singing
"Happy Birthday" in my dream.

08:32.971 --> 08:34.848
And before it was over,
I saw that your head

08:34.889 --> 08:36.599
was a crumpled
piece of paper, man!

08:36.641 --> 08:38.935
What the hell
do you think that means?

08:38.977 --> 08:40.270
Oh, my God, oh, my God,
oh, my God, oh, my God!

08:40.311 --> 08:41.855
- I did not mention
my past as a Frías,

08:41.896 --> 08:43.565
and he didn't ask.

08:43.606 --> 08:44.858
He always looked ahead.

08:44.899 --> 08:47.569
[fireworks booming]
all: Whoa!

08:47.610 --> 08:49.654
- Aww.

08:51.781 --> 08:55.285
- Alex wanted to create
memories for our guests,

08:55.326 --> 08:58.580
but in doing so, he created
a home for his employees.

08:58.621 --> 09:00.749
- [farts]
- Oh, what the fuck, Alex?

09:00.790 --> 09:02.542
He just farted here.
- [laughs]

09:02.584 --> 09:04.127
- The fuck is wrong with you?

09:04.169 --> 09:05.378
- [speaking Spanish]

09:05.420 --> 09:07.422
- But are we made
only of memories?

09:07.464 --> 09:10.342
all: Oceana Vista!

09:10.383 --> 09:11.593
- Whoo!
- Let's see.

09:11.634 --> 09:14.763
[applause]

09:17.349 --> 09:19.768
I fucked it up.
All right, one more time.

09:19.809 --> 09:21.561
- Okay.
- Ah!

09:21.603 --> 09:25.648
All right, tres, dos, uno!

09:25.690 --> 09:27.567
all: Oceana Vista!

09:27.609 --> 09:28.943
[camera shutter snaps]

09:28.985 --> 09:30.320
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

09:30.362 --> 09:33.281
[applause]

09:37.827 --> 09:40.622
- Five years. Five.

09:40.663 --> 09:42.207
[together] Five!
- Whoo!

09:42.248 --> 09:45.085
- The Oceana Vista
is a manifestation

09:45.126 --> 09:48.546
of a dream, of a memory haven.

09:48.588 --> 09:50.215
Uh...

09:57.806 --> 09:59.891
I love, uh...

10:01.476 --> 10:02.977
The...

10:11.486 --> 10:14.447
[eerie music]

10:14.489 --> 10:21.371
* *

10:42.392 --> 10:44.144
[mumbling]

10:45.270 --> 10:47.105
[music stops]
- Are you okay, Alex?

10:47.147 --> 10:48.106
- Uh--

10:48.148 --> 10:51.443
- What?

10:51.484 --> 10:53.695
What?

10:58.783 --> 11:01.703
- Stop fucking looking at me!

11:07.208 --> 11:09.252
- Alex!

11:09.294 --> 11:12.213
[waves crashing]

11:23.099 --> 11:24.434
[sighs]

11:27.228 --> 11:30.106
How are you doing, my friend?

11:30.148 --> 11:31.816
- You ever feel like
something from the past

11:31.858 --> 11:34.736
is missing from the future?

11:39.908 --> 11:42.452
I have memory leakage.

11:42.494 --> 11:43.870
- Hmm, yeah.

11:43.912 --> 11:46.498
Sometimes I forget things, too.

11:46.539 --> 11:49.376
I found that writing notes
to myself helps a lot.

11:49.417 --> 11:51.836
Post-its.
- No, you don't understand.

11:51.878 --> 11:54.714
I have memory leakage.

11:54.756 --> 11:56.508
- Leakage?
- Yeah, from my ears.

11:56.549 --> 12:00.720
This is a condition called
Tempus Exhaurire.

12:00.762 --> 12:03.765
From my ears, from my ass...

12:07.435 --> 12:09.104
Everywhere.

12:13.900 --> 12:16.111
- I've never heard
of Tempus Ex--

12:16.152 --> 12:18.863
is that some kind of amnesia?

12:22.826 --> 12:25.036
- I want to show you something.

12:25.078 --> 12:28.289
[mellow music]

12:28.331 --> 12:30.458
* *

12:30.500 --> 12:33.795
It's my attempt to...

12:33.837 --> 12:36.548
preserve my memories.

12:36.589 --> 12:39.426
- What do you mean?

12:39.467 --> 12:42.762
- People, places--
all my memories documented.

12:42.804 --> 12:45.098
The hippocampus,
it's the brain's pantry.

12:45.140 --> 12:46.725
We need to keep it stocked.

12:46.766 --> 12:53.940
* *

12:54.441 --> 12:58.945
I'm beginning to lose the sense
of who I am, Baltasar.

12:58.987 --> 13:00.905
I need your help
to pick up the pieces.

13:00.947 --> 13:03.116
I don't trust anyone else.

13:03.158 --> 13:04.784
My appetite makes no sense.

13:04.826 --> 13:06.578
I have a primal hatred
of iguanas

13:06.619 --> 13:07.871
I just don't understand.

13:07.912 --> 13:10.832
And I'm--I just want
to be a kid again.

13:10.874 --> 13:13.960
And I...

13:14.002 --> 13:16.379
I don't remember my family.

13:19.257 --> 13:21.885
- Well, maybe we should
at least tell Luna?

13:21.926 --> 13:23.511
- No, it's just--

13:23.553 --> 13:25.138
no one will understand.

13:25.180 --> 13:28.725
- I do not understand, Alex.

13:28.767 --> 13:30.435
- You will someday, though.

13:32.687 --> 13:36.024
- I don't know.
Um...

13:36.066 --> 13:37.942
This is really fucked up.

13:37.984 --> 13:42.489
Maybe if we ask for help
or talk to a doctor

13:42.530 --> 13:46.743
or if you change your diet,
you know, take some medication.

13:46.785 --> 13:48.787
- I know you're a Frías.

13:48.828 --> 13:52.874
* *

13:52.916 --> 13:55.460
I knew the moment I met you.

13:55.502 --> 13:58.546
You have the fucking
bone structure of a Frías.

13:58.588 --> 14:01.466
And nobody wakes up
dressed like you.

14:01.508 --> 14:05.178
But then your brother Alonso
came to the resort

14:05.220 --> 14:07.263
offering me
the deal of the century

14:07.305 --> 14:10.225
on Frías-sewn uniforms
if I fired you.

14:11.101 --> 14:13.395
It was a shakedown.

14:14.938 --> 14:19.275
Ask me what I told him.

14:19.317 --> 14:20.860
- What did you say to him?

14:20.902 --> 14:23.405
- I told him
"Fuck the fuck off."

14:23.446 --> 14:26.658
* *

14:26.700 --> 14:28.410
No more secrets between us.

14:28.451 --> 14:30.870
We're all we have.
I need you.

14:30.912 --> 14:32.872
Right?

14:32.914 --> 14:35.041
- I'm--I'm here for you.

14:36.584 --> 14:38.420
- I'm sorry.

14:40.130 --> 14:43.758
- That's when I knew Alex's
condition would be a problem.

14:43.800 --> 14:45.927
The leak became a flood.

14:45.969 --> 14:47.595
It affected the resort.

14:49.597 --> 14:52.726
Renovations started,
but never finished.

14:52.767 --> 14:55.061
Bills went unpaid.

14:55.103 --> 14:56.563
He turned on the staff,

14:56.604 --> 15:00.400
accusing them of stealing
to him, lying to him.

15:00.442 --> 15:01.776
- Memory leakage.

15:01.818 --> 15:04.446
- Yeah, memory leakage.

15:06.322 --> 15:09.242
I never thought Alex
was capable of

15:09.284 --> 15:11.327
being a dangerous man, but...

15:13.830 --> 15:16.166
Then came the iguanas.

15:29.220 --> 15:31.389
- I had to honor
my friend's secret,

15:31.431 --> 15:33.933
but I was asking myself, why?

15:33.975 --> 15:36.770
[tense music]

15:36.811 --> 15:38.730
Over the course of that year,

15:38.772 --> 15:42.442
he retreated to his penthouse,
a recluse, unraveling,

