19:34.215 --> 19:35.800
- Excuse me, señorita,
can I ask you

19:35.842 --> 19:37.677
for a photo of Sam
that I can see?

19:37.719 --> 19:38.678
- Yeah.

19:40.555 --> 19:43.933
- Was that photo of his own
penis or someone else's penis?

19:43.975 --> 19:45.477
- Oh, my God!

19:45.518 --> 19:47.270
- Well, I don't know.
It could have been Sam's.

19:47.312 --> 19:48.271
It could have been
someone else's.

19:48.313 --> 19:49.773
I don't know what's worse.

19:49.814 --> 19:51.816
I don't know which
I'd rather it be.

19:51.858 --> 19:53.610
It might have been
a little small.

19:53.651 --> 19:56.363
- Oh.
- Maybe a little big for Sam.

19:56.404 --> 19:59.324
[laughs]
I--um...

19:59.366 --> 20:01.493
oh, I don't know.

20:01.534 --> 20:03.870
- Just stop.
- What do you think?

20:03.912 --> 20:07.082
- Hmm?
- Were you two having problems?

20:07.123 --> 20:08.625
- No.
- No?

20:08.667 --> 20:09.584
- No. God, no.

20:09.626 --> 20:11.211
No, we've been
together forever.

20:11.252 --> 20:13.171
And I'm here on vacation
with his family.

20:13.213 --> 20:14.506
And, you know,
we're always talking

20:14.547 --> 20:16.341
about marriage, you know?

20:16.383 --> 20:17.634
He's saying,
"I want to marry you."

20:17.676 --> 20:19.636
- And what do you say to him
about marriage?

20:19.678 --> 20:21.471
- Yeah, yeah--
no, yeah, I mean, it's--

20:21.513 --> 20:22.555
well, 'cause we have
a lot of time.

20:22.597 --> 20:23.807
We're young.
But we've been together--

20:23.848 --> 20:25.308
it's like, it could--

20:25.350 --> 20:27.227
I don't know what you guys
are staring at.

20:30.021 --> 20:31.398
- What are you thinking?

20:31.439 --> 20:35.443
- I was surprised when
I saw it on his phone, okay?

20:35.485 --> 20:37.320
I was surprised.
I didn't immediately go,

20:37.362 --> 20:39.030
"Jan, look, a penis."
- Don't lie to me.

20:39.072 --> 20:41.241
- Maybe the penis was,
like, an art channel.

20:41.282 --> 20:44.160
- Is this your--your son?

20:44.202 --> 20:46.413
- Sí.
- Yeah.

20:46.454 --> 20:48.748
- Can I keep this?

20:48.790 --> 20:50.709
- Yeah, mm-hmm.

21:19.154 --> 21:20.739
- [exhales heavily]

23:12.934 --> 23:16.229
- Oh.
Hello again, Mr. Thompson.

23:16.271 --> 23:19.274
I am Detective
Baltasar Peniche,

23:19.315 --> 23:20.942
Oceana Vista head of security.

23:20.984 --> 23:22.318
- Oh.
- Can I come in?

23:22.360 --> 23:24.112
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah?

23:24.154 --> 23:26.156
Did you enjoy the mezcal?

23:26.197 --> 23:27.949
- Uh, well, I finished it.

23:27.991 --> 23:29.576
- Ah.

23:29.617 --> 23:33.580
Listen, I was wondering if
I could speak to your daughter?

23:33.621 --> 23:37.250
- Um, what is this about?

23:37.292 --> 23:39.502
- Another guest is trying
to locate their son,

23:39.544 --> 23:42.213
and your daughter
was the last person...

23:42.255 --> 23:43.131
- Hey, Vi?
[knocking on door]

23:43.173 --> 23:44.132
- He was seen with.

23:44.174 --> 23:45.759
[foreboding music]

23:45.800 --> 23:47.635
- Oh.

23:47.677 --> 23:49.137
Oh, no.

23:50.680 --> 23:52.766
Where is she?

23:52.807 --> 23:56.269
