The sad truth is that

35:57.574 --> 36:01.745
if you cut the head off
an iguana,

36:01.786 --> 36:03.371
it will die.

36:05.707 --> 36:08.710
- [laughs]
Okay.

36:08.752 --> 36:13.006
So--so you lied to the police,

36:13.048 --> 36:14.758
to the--
- The parents.

36:14.799 --> 36:19.220
- The parents, to everyone,
to protect a guy who said

36:19.262 --> 36:23.266
that his memory was leaking
out of his fucking ears?

36:23.308 --> 36:26.269
Come on!
- This is a crime scene.

36:26.311 --> 36:28.521
- Oh, this is something, yes.
- This is all a crime scene.

36:28.563 --> 36:30.148
- Wait, wait, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey, listen.

36:30.190 --> 36:33.109
I'm almost, almost done, yes?

36:35.653 --> 36:38.990
I spent a year

36:39.032 --> 36:43.578
studying this mural,
looking for a clue.

36:43.620 --> 36:45.747
- Just emptying out
what's left.

36:45.789 --> 36:49.042
[gentle music]

36:49.084 --> 36:52.379
- I could tell he wasn't there.

36:52.420 --> 36:55.131
He was lost
in a different time.

36:55.173 --> 36:58.093
I saw his memory drain.

36:58.134 --> 37:01.304
But maybe this was different.

37:01.346 --> 37:05.725
Maybe this was the memory
of the Oceana Vista

37:05.767 --> 37:08.728
or maybe something else.

37:08.770 --> 37:12.315
[sighs]
But no.

37:12.357 --> 37:15.318
This was not the work
of a man

37:15.360 --> 37:19.781
with any profound insight
into the human condition.

37:19.823 --> 37:23.743
These was
the meaningless scribbles

37:23.785 --> 37:27.580
of a crazy person.

37:27.622 --> 37:30.166
So I made a mistake.

37:31.835 --> 37:36.673
I was looking for an answer
where there was none.

37:40.468 --> 37:43.596
But today,

37:43.638 --> 37:46.057
I realize...

37:52.522 --> 37:53.857
I was wrong.

37:53.898 --> 37:54.941
[object clatters]
- [gasps]

37:54.983 --> 37:56.568
- Holy shit.

37:56.609 --> 37:59.195
- Uno, dos, tres.

37:59.237 --> 38:02.157
[upbeat Latin music]

